â”€â”€ Nei's IELTS Writing Cheatsheet (Weakness Fix Version) â”€â”€

1) Capitalisation:
   I / Excel / For instance.

2) Plurals:
   ideas / risks / skills / companies.
   (rule: general statements â†’ plural)

3) Tenses:
   general truths â†’ present simple.
   (young people take risks / older people prefer stability)

4) Articles:
   a = first mention
   the = second mention or specific
   Ã˜ = uncountable (job satisfaction, education)

5) Spelling list:
   satisfaction / planning / instance / attention / retirement.

6) Natural expressions:
   more likely to / tend to / repetitive tasks / tech professional.

7) Sentence structure:
   Use and/but/because/while to join full clauses.
